-- Turkey's Halkbank to raise paid-in capital to 2.25 bln lira to set up Islamic lender
-- By Ayla Jean Yackley
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 11:14AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Dec 19 (Reuters) - State-run lender Halkbank <HALKB.IS> said on Friday it would increase its paid-in capital by 80 percent to 2.25 billion lira ($972.4 million) to set up an Islamic lender.

The bank made the announcement in a filing with the stock exchange. Turkey has four non-state Islamic banks, and state Ziraat Bank has received regulatory approval to establish an Islamic finance unit as well.